Our Story

A secret valley
where time slows down

Tucked between Sintra's mystical hills and Ericeira's Atlantic coast, Casas do Rio Verde is a pair of handcrafted cottages wrapped in oak, olive and fig trees — with a river babbling just below.

Whether you're waking to birdsong, picking figs for breakfast, or soaking under a star-lit sky in the wood-fired hot tub — this is the kind of slow that restores you completely.

The Cottages

Two houses,
one valley

Ninho
★ 5.0 · Guest Favourite

O Ninho

Natural Chalet in the Forest Valley

"The Nest" sits nestled among ancient oaks, draped in climbing vines with its own private hot tub. Wake to the sound of the river, fall asleep to nothing but owls and stars. A cosy retreat for couples craving deep nature.

Wood-fired hot tub Private terrace Forest views River access Pet-friendly

Casinha
★ 5.0 · Guest Favourite

A Casinha

The Little Stone House by the Mill

"A Casinha da Azenha" is a beautifully restored stone cottage with a sun-drenched terrace, wicker seating and instant access to the shared pool and gardens. History, comfort and wild nature in perfect balance.

Stone architecture Outdoor kitchen Pool access Lounge terrace Pet-friendly

Life Here

What awaits you

♨️

Hot Tub Under Stars

Sink into the wood-fired hot tub as dusk settles over the valley. Steam rising, stars appearing one by one — this is the memory you'll carry home.

🌊

River Hammock

A net hammock suspended over the stream — the most unexpected and wonderful afternoon you'll ever spend horizontal, with river sounds and dappled light.

🦋

Wild Nature

Old-growth butterflies, salamanders in mossy streams, swallowtails on wildflowers. Nature documentaries happen outside your door here.

🫒

Garden & Orchard

Pick figs, loquats and pomegranates. Gather wildflowers. The garden is yours — unstructured and abundant, the way good gardens should be.

🏊

Pool & Loungers

A turquoise pool glimpsed through rustling oak leaves. Wooden loungers, a parasol, a cold drink — summer in Portugal in its purest form.

🗺️

Perfect Base

Sintra's palaces, Ericeira's surf, Mafra's monastery, Lisbon's tiles. Everything is 20–45 minutes away, yet here feels completely apart from it all.
